==English==

===Noun===

{{en-noun|-}}

# {{grammar}} The form in which the subject of a verb performs some action upon itself.
Examples: 
#:[[active voice]]: ''Fred shaved John.''
#:[[passive voice]]: ''John was shaved by Fred.''
#:[[middle voice]]: ''Fred shaved (himself).''

====Usage note====
English once did but no longer has a middle (sometimes called the [[mediopassive]]) voice, but the example demonstrates how it works. For highly inflected languages like ancient Greek, the middle voice has its own distinct verb form. For English, it's just a grammatical oddity dealt with by use of a reflexive pronoun. We might also mention the grammatical notion of [[topic]]; here, Fred is the topic, even though he's been moved from subjective to objective case and who knows what when dealing with the middle voice.